CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1955, pg. 13 reads: "Masonic banquet At Gateway Plaza - Hiram Grand Lodge, AF&AM, and auxiliaries, held a banquet at Gateway Plaza Sunday. Left to right: Past Master A.E. Nix, Past Master Milton Owens, Atty. Henry Smith, Prothonotary David B. Roberts, Councilman Paul F. Jones, Charles pg. Pernell, Mrs. Esther Green, Grand Matron; Grand Master Herbert Towns, Mrs. Earnestine Towne, Royal Matron; Mrs. Anna Bolden, Heroines Matron; Sir Knight Richard Bolden, Mrs. Luella Lane, Grand Matron of Daughters of Sphinx. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groups of men, and women, including one wearing light colored dress, corsage, and dark hat with veil, seated at banquet table in Gateway Center for Hiram Grand Lodge masonic banquet
